column1: ##DESCRIPTION=ID=ID of the variant, often dbSNP rsnumber
##DESCRIPTION=GENEINFO=Pairs each of gene symbol:gene id.  The gene symbol and id are delimited by a colon (:) and each pair is delimited by a vertical bar (|)
##DESCRIPTION=SAO=Variant Allele Origin: 0 - unspecified, 1 - Germline, 2 - Somatic, 3 - Both
##DESCRIPTION=SSR=Variant Suspect Reason Codes (may be more than one value added together) 0 - unspecified, 1 - Paralog, 2 - byEST, 4 - oldAlign, 8 - Para_EST, 16 - 1kg_failed, 1024 - other
##DESCRIPTION=GMAF=Global Minor Allele Frequency [0, 0.5]; global population is 1000GenomesProject phase 1 genotype data from 629 individuals, released in the 11-23-2012 dataset
##DESCRIPTION=WGT=Weight, 00 - unmapped, 1 - weight 1, 2 - weight 2, 3 - weight 3 or more
##DESCRIPTION=TPA=Provisional Third Party Annotation(TPA) (currently rs from PHARMGKB who will give phenotype data)
##DESCRIPTION=NSF=Has non-synonymous frameshift A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes all downstream amino acids. FxnClas
##DESCRIPTION=NSM=Has non-synonymous missense A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes protein peptide. FxnClas
##DESCRIPTION=NSN=Has non-synonymous nonsense A coding region variation where one allele in the set changes to STOP codon (TER). FxnClas
##DESCRIPTION=REF=Has reference A coding region variation where one allele in the set is identical to the reference sequence. FxnCod
##DESCRIPTION=SYN=Has synonymous A coding region variation where one allele in the set does not change the encoded amino acid. FxnCod
##DESCRIPTION=U3=In 3' UTR Location is in an untranslated region (UTR). FxnCod
##DESCRIPTION=U5=In 5' UTR Location is in an untranslated region (UTR). FxnCod
##DESCRIPTION=OTH=Has other variant with exactly the same set of mapped positions on NCBI refernce assembly.
##DESCRIPTION=CFL=Has Assembly conflict. This is for weight 1 and 2 variant that maps to different chromosomes on different assemblies.
##DESCRIPTION=ASP=Is Assembly specific. This is set if the variant only maps to one assembly
##DESCRIPTION=MUT=Is mutation (journal citation, explicit fact): a low frequency variation that is cited in journal and other reputable sources
##DESCRIPTION=VLD=Is Validated.  This bit is set if the variant has 2+ minor allele count based on frequency or genotype data.
##DESCRIPTION=G5A=>5% minor allele frequency in each and all populations
##DESCRIPTION=HD=Marker is on high density genotyping kit (50K density or greater).  The variant may have phenotype associations present in dbGaP.
##DESCRIPTION=GNO=Genotypes available. The variant has individual genotype (in SubInd table).
##DESCRIPTION=CDA=Variation is interrogated in a clinical diagnostic assay
##DESCRIPTION=NOC=Contig allele not present in variant allele list. The reference sequence allele at the mapped position is not present in the variant allele list, adjusted for orientation.
##DESCRIPTION=WTD=Is Withdrawn by submitter If one member ss is withdrawn by submitter, then this bit is set.  If all member ss' are withdrawn, then the rs is deleted to SNPHistory
##DESCRIPTION=NOV=Rs cluster has non-overlapping allele sets. True when rs set has more than 2 alleles from different submissions and these sets share no alleles in common.
##DESCRIPTION=GCF=Has Genotype Conflict Same (rs, ind), different genotype.  N/N is not included.
##DESCRIPTION=CLNHGVS=Variant names from HGVS.    The order of these variants corresponds to the order of the info in the other clinical  INFO tags.

##DESCRIPTION=CLNALLE=Variant alleles from REF or ALT columns.  0 is REF, 1 is the first ALT allele, etc.  This is used to match alleles with other corresponding clinical (CLN) INFO tags.  A value of -1 indicates that no allele was found to match a corresponding HGVS allele name.

##DESCRIPTION=CLNORIGIN=Allele Origin. One or more of the following values may be added: 0 - unknown; 1 - germline; 2 - somatic; 4 - inherited; 8 - paternal; 16 - maternal; 32 - de-novo; 64 - biparental; 128 - uniparental; 256 - not-tested; 512 - tested-inconclusive; 1073741824 - other

##DESCRIPTION=CLNSIG=Variant Clinical Significance, 0 - unknown, 1 - untested, 2 - non-pathogenic, 3 - probable-non-pathogenic, 4 - probable-pathogenic, 5 - pathogenic, 6 - drug-response, 7 - histocompatibility, 255 - other
##FILTER=NC=Inconsistent Genotype Submission For At Least One Sample
